ional name for a maker of them.","English: perhaps from the Old French personal name <i>Gerland</i> (ancient Germanic <i>Garuland</i>, probably from <i>garw-</i> ‘war-gear; prepared(ness)’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’; the first element of the French name may instead be from a name beginning with <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’).","English: topographic name from Middle English <i>gor(e)</i>, <i>gar(e)</i> ‘triangular piece’ + <i>lond</i> ‘land’ (Old English <i>gāra</i> + <i>land</i>, <i>lond</i>), for someone who lived ‘(at the) triangular piece of land’. Compare   Garfield  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gerland","meanings":["English (North Yorkshire and Lancashire): variant of   Garland  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Garfield","meanings":["English (Midlands): topographic name from Middle English <i>gor(e)</i>, <i>gar(e)</i> ‘triangular piece’ + <i>feld</i> ‘open country, field’ (Old English <i>gār</i> + <i>feld</i>), for someone who lived by a triangular piece of land.","English: alternatively, sometimes perhaps a variant of   Carville   (a name of Norman origin), with excrescent final <i>-d</i>.","Americanized form of one or more similar (like-sounding) Jewish surnames."]},{"name":"Gartland","meanings":["Irish and English: variant of   Garland  .","Irish (northern Leinster and southern Ulster): shortened Anglicized form of <b>Mac Gearnúin</b>, a patronymic from the Norman personal name   Gernon  ."]}]},{"name":"Guillaume","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Germanic.  See  <b>William</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"William","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Guillaume de Garlande III was born about 1140, in Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, France. He had at least 1 daughter with Alix de Chatillon. He died in 1200, at the age of 61."},"et":{"Abt 1140–1200":"umbes 1140–1200","1172–1216":"1172–1216","1193–1249":"1193–1249","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1249":"1249","1216":"1216","Abt 1140":"umbes 1140","1200":"1200","1140":"1140","1172":"1172","1193":"1193","ABT 1193":"umbes 1193","Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, Île-de-France, France":"Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, Prantsusmaa","Of, Gournay, Seine-Et-Oise, France":"Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1140–1200":"noin 1140–1200","1172–1216":"1172–1216","1193–1249":"1193–1249","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1249":"1249","1216":"1216","Abt 1140":"noin 1140","1200":"1200","1140":"1140","1172":"1172","1193":"1193","ABT 1193":"noin 1193","Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, Île-de-France, France":"Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, Ranska","Of, Gournay, Seine-Et-Oise, France":"Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, Ranska"},"fr":{"Abt 1140–1200":"environ 1140–1200","1172–1216":"1172–1216","1193–1249":"1193–1249","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1249":"1249","1216":"1216","Abt 1140":"environ 1140","1200":"1200","1140":"1140","1172":"1172","1193":"1193","ABT 1193":"environ 1193","Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, Île-de-France, France":"Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, France","Of, Gournay, Seine-Et-Oise, France":"Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, France","lifeSummary":"Guillaume de Garlande III est né environ 1140, à Gournay, Seine-et-Oise, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Alix de Chatillon. Il est décédé en 1200, à l’âge de 61 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1140–1200":"um 1140–1200","1172–1216":"1172–1216","1193–1249":"1193–1249","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1249":"1249","1216":"1216","Abt 1140":"um 1140","1200